               <div class="btArticleContent ">
                  <div class="bt_bb_wrapper">
                  <div class="bodytext contentText"> <p>Many of us don’t think about our air conditioner until something goes wrong. However, maintenance is the most effective way to prevent potentially expensive repairs.</p> </div>
                 <div class="bodytext contentText"> <p><span style="font-weight: bold;"><br>1. Clogged filter</span></p><p>This is by far the most common cause of furnace malfunctions. A clogged filter prevents air from circulating through the system effectively, which means your furnace has to work harder to heat your home. Over time, this damages the unit and raises your heating costs.<br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">2. Faulty thermostat</span></p><p>If your furnace runs constantly or doesn’t heat rooms enough, the issue could be with the thermostat. Although this common problem doesn’t require <a href="//<?php echo $_SERVER['SERVER_NAME']; ?>/furnace-repair-replacement-winnipeg" data-track-event="click" data-track-action="internal_link_clicked">an emergency repair</a>, failing to deal with it could damage your furnace over time.<br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">3. Pilot light malfunction</span></p><p>If the thermostat is working properly but you’re still not getting sufficient heat from your furnace, the pilot light is likely to blame. Its function is to ignite the fuel in your furnace, so your home can’t be heated without it. Luckily, this is usually an easy fix.<br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">4. Broken blower motor</span></p><p>Without a functioning blower motor, your furnace can’t push warm air through the ducts and into your home. If your furnace isn’t supplying enough heat and you’ve eliminated the issues listed above, chances are you need to hire a professional to remove the old blower motor and install a new one.<br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">5. Wear and tear</span></p><p>Sometimes a furnace exhibits problems as it approaches the end of its lifespan. However, this seldom causes a lack of warm air. It’s common, however, for a furnace to become less and less efficient as it gets older. An inefficient use of fuel results in higher heating bills. Your furnace also has to work harder to sufficiently heat your home, which exacerbates wear and tear.<br><br>Furnaces require increasingly frequent repairs over time and problems may become too costly to fix. Parts might be hard to find for an obsolete model. If this is the case, it might be time to consider <a href="//<?php echo $_SERVER['SERVER_NAME']; ?>/furnace-installation-winnipeg" data-track-event="click" data-track-action="internal_link_clicked">installing a new furnace</a>.<br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Furnace Repair Experts in Winnipeg</span></p><p>The next time your furnace malfunctions, get in touch with the professionals at <a href="/" data-track-event="click" data-track-action="internal_link_clicked">East Side Ventilation</a>. We offer a variety of furnace repair, cleaning and maintenance services, and if your unit needs to be replaced, you can count on our experts to offer reliable advice. For more information or to schedule an appointment, <a href="/winnipeg-hvac-company-contact" data-track-event="click" data-track-action="internal_link_clicked">contact us today</a>.</p><p>&nbsp;</p> </div>
